        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 14 at 12:25PM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 1225 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Schroeder, or 13 miles northeast of Goliad, moving northeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mission Valley, Schroeder, and Ander.

This includes US Highway 77 between mile markers 580 and 582.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
